So you think asking for any modifications in a restaurant is rude? Hmmm. I don't usually, but have been known to ask for NO SUGAR in coffee, tea and iced tea in places that usually add it. I  like sweet things as a rule and even some sweet drinks, but for some reason casnot stand sweet tea or coffee. We had a beloved Lebanese restaurant when we lived in Chicago, but they kept not getting my request for the coffee. Finally i overheard the waiter saying "bila sukari", which awakened my long-lost meagre knowledge of Swahili, and now I always get Turkish/Greek/Arab coffee the way I like it.
